						               													<description>Boardgame for 2 &amp;ndash; 4 children (Ages 6 to 10) in which they have to manage their pocket money. Thematically based on a fun-fair visit during the holidays the players have to spend their money on various items. But with their limited amount of money they can't afford everything they want - they have to earn some money. Only if they are able to manage their pocket money successfully will they win the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay:&amp;#10;The players start with a given amount of pocket money and move across the board rolling one dice (d6). Movement is allowed in any direction and players may move less spaces than their dice roll. On special card fields they are able to fulfill six actions (spending money on several items and earning money to afford them) which are needed to win the game. The placement of the action cards is strictly ruled - making following-up cards harder to buy things (prices will rise) and harder to earn money (earnings will decrease). After each players' turn the turn marker is moved one day further. When the 7th turn ends (= one week) all players receive a new amount of pocket money.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player who has fulfilled all his actions, wins. If there is a tie, the player with most of the cash wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
